						               													<description>Almost nothing has changed in the City version of the Mafia card game since  1980s... But what if there was a new version of  Mafia, where the game experience becomes more diverse, unused and balanced with each card having a special ability... A team of players with 5 years of experience playing Mafia  came up with an advanced version of Mafia... Our team has tested this version of Mafia in London for the last half a year. The result is that after playing Fantasy Mafia no one wanted to play the usual city  Mafia ever again. The cards for this Mafia are for sale in two languages &amp;#226;&amp;#128;&amp;#139;&amp;#226;&amp;#128;&amp;#139;&amp;#226;&amp;#128;&amp;#139;&amp;#226;&amp;#128;&amp;#139;(English and Russian).There are also two different card designs themed in &amp;quot;Fantasy&amp;quot; and &amp;quot;Science fiction&amp;quot; settings. The cards also exist in two formats - &amp;quot;Poker&amp;quot; size  and &amp;quot;Tarot &amp;quot; size.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The differences from Standard Mafia card games :&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Different timeline settings - this version of Mafia has either :&amp;#10;&amp;#10;&amp;#10;     High Fantasy styled cards&amp;#10;     Science fiction styled cards&amp;#10;&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Ordinary city Mafia cards do not have &amp;quot; abilities&amp;quot; written on them.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;In this version of Mafia each Card has a different ability, so up to 21 abilities per pack of 21 cards.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Some &amp;quot;abilities&amp;quot; examples:&amp;#10;&amp;#10;&amp;#10;     &amp;quot; After the death a player gains a new card chosen from 5&amp;quot;&amp;#10;     &amp;quot;The Player can choose whom he starts the game as Mafia, Killer or Villager &amp;quot;   &amp;#10;&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
